sections.Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG):
RAG combines retrieval of relevant code snippets with LLM generation to produce contextually grounded completions. Architecture: Indexing: All project code is chunked, embedded, and stored in vector DB with metadata (file path, language, function boundaries). Retrieval: When a completion is requested, the current code context is embedded and used to query top-k similar snippets from the vector DB. Metadata filters ensure results match the same language. Augmentation: Retrieved snippets are inserted into the prompt as context: "Here are similar code patterns from your project:

{retrieved_code}

Now complete this code:" Generation: LLM generates completion with the enriched context, producing suggestions that follow project-specific patterns and conventions. Benefits: (1) 40% more relevant completions on project-specific code, (2) Learns project conventions without fine-tuning, (3) Works across languages without model retraining, (4) Provides transparency — users can see which code influenced the suggestion. Challenges: Retrieval latency adds 50-150ms. Implement caching for frequent code patterns. Use hybrid search (keyword + semantic) for better precision. Implement re-ranking with cross-encoder for top-3 results.
